title: Hands Off Medicaid Rally!
description:
Drastic cuts to the federal budget are underway and we are standing up to say:

Hands Off Medicaid!

1.2 million Minnesotans rely on Medicaid (aka Medical Assistance) in some way. Proposed cuts to Medicaid are estimated to cost Minnesotans up to $1.6 Billion per year in federal funds.

title: Republicans for Medicaid Roundtable
description:
As House and Senate Republicans advance a federal budget that proposes $1.5 trillion in cuts to vital programs like Medicaid, Republican seniors and community leaders in Pennsylvania are speaking out. Join the Pennsylvania Alliance for Retired Americans (PARA) for a virtual roundtable highlighting the voices of Republican voters who reject these devastating cuts and support preserving Medicaid for their families and communities.

Medicaid is a lifeline for over 400,000 seniors in Pennsylvania and supports 5 out of every 8 nursing home residents. While congressional Republicans push for cuts, polling shows that most Republican voters‚Äîincluding Trump supporters‚Äîoppose slashing Medicaid and understand its critical role in local health care systems.

This event will feature testimony from Republican retirees, caregivers, and advocates calling on lawmakers to protect Medicaid. Together, we‚Äôll make clear that the fight to save Medicaid is not a partisan issue‚Äîit‚Äôs a moral one.

Who Should Attend:
Community members, advocates, media, and anyone concerned about the future of health care and retirement security in Pennsylvania.

Join your friends and neighbors at Sister District Project San Francisco for the #NoKings mass protest and day of defiance!

description:
In 2024 Democrats assumed that our base would turn out in large numbers to support our Democratic candidates. They didn‚Äôt. These voters are a very important part of our local, state, and national success.  Our guest, Linda Morales, will explain why we must work to turn out those voters, how we can do that.

Linda Morales stands as one of Texas‚Äôs most fearless and visionary advocates for civil rights, a trailblazer whose legacy is etched in the fight for Latino, women‚Äôs, LGBTQIA+, and workers' rights. As a fierce union organizer, Morales led campaigns for the National AFL-CIO, SEIU Local 1, Sheet Metal Workers International Union, and California Nurses Association/National Nurses United, organizing workers across industries and empowering them to build collective strength.

Her commitment to social justice also includes a broad range of professional experience in healthcare, government, and labor. She worked as a Legislative Assistant in the Texas Legislature, served as a Television Specialist for the Texas Health Report with Dr ‚ÄúRed‚Äù Duke, produced MIDDAY for the Texas Medical Center, and edited What Goes On, a newsletter for healthcare professionals.

Currently, she continues her work with the Texas Gulf Coast Area Labor Federation/AFL-CIO (TGCALF) and has launched a column titled Raise the Mic, a Facebook space dedicated to speaking out against injustice. Change doesn't happen in silence‚Äîit happens when we stand together, amplify each other's voices, and demand better. Raise the Mic is my contribution to that movement, and I hope it inspires others to do the same.

title: Food Distribution Prepping - SF Democratic Party - Democrats on the Move
description:
As part of the Democrats on the Move campaign for May, the SF Democratic Party will be in the Portola/Viz Valley area. As the economy is becoming less predictable, lower income households will be hit hard by rising food costs. That's why we're partnering with Family Connections to help prepare food bags for distribution.

Volunteering will be on Friday, May 9, 11 am - 12 pm at 2565 San Bruno Ave. Check in with Tram, FCC Family Support Coordinator. Wear comfortable shoes. Volunteers will help to assemble bulk produce and pantry items into ~125 bags, which will be distributed to families later that day.

Family Connections is a nonprofit that operates three family resource centers in the Portola, Excelsior, and Visitacion Valley neighborhoods of San Francisco, serving over 2,200 individuals annually. We provide community-driven, multilingual education and support programs to ensure families can thrive. Our vision is for a connected, equitable community where every child and family can access the resources they need.

For more info on Family Connections: http://fccenters.org/

For more info on Democrats on the Move: https://www.sfdems.org/onthemove
